Justice A.Y Ameenullahi of an Area Court in Ilorin has jailed a 38-year-old man, Olawale Samuel for six months imprisonment for stealing a he-goat. The convict, a resident of Amulegbolola Compound Ogbomoso, Oyo state, was dragged to the Area Court for ‘being in possession’, contrary to section 319 of the penal code law. The Police FIR revealed that Samuel confessed that he stole the goat in Geri-Alimi Area, Ilorin and brought it to Oja-Oba for sale. The case was prosecuted on behalf of the police by Inspector Oderinde Abideen. In his judgement, the trial judge, A.Y Ameenullahi sentenced accused to six month imprisonment with an option of N20,000 fine.   By Demola Akinyemi, Ilorin. Justice Muhammed Sani of the Federal High Court in Ilorin on Monday convicted a 26-year-old Computer Engineer, Olabisi Damilola Samuel from Boluwaduro Local Government Area of Osun State and two others over offences bordering on cybercrime and retention of proceeds of unlawful activities. The two others… In "News" Justice Adenike Akinpelu of the Kwara State High Court has revoked the bail bond entered into, by two civil servants in the state over the disappearance of their sureties undergoing trial by Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) In "News" The Court of Appeal Sitting in Gombe on Friday sentenced Ma’aji Shettima Arfo, the former General Manager of Maiduguri Flour Mills to 7 years imprisonment for allegedly stealing millions of Naira belonging to the Borno State Government and the Flour mills of Nigeria while he was the General manager of… In "News"